HhsHccPatientsRegistryDataMart

HhsHccPatientsRegistryDataMart is loaded from DM_HHS_HCC and DM_HHS_HCC_2. DM_HHS_HCC and DM_HHS_HCC_2 are Clarity data marts that store information related to the HHS-HCC Registry metrics. Each row represents metric data for a patient for a specific timespan. This table consolidates data about the applicability of hierarchical conditions categories (HCCs), most recent related diagnosis information, and whether or not the patient requires a calendar year refresh for each applicable HCC. For each HCC category, this information is consolidated into the corresponding EpicStatus column. Only patients that meet specific inclusion criteria have information stored in this table.

Properties

Reporting table name
dbo.HhsHccPatientsRegistryDataMart
Granularity
One row per patient, per timespan
Links to
  1. DiagnosisDim
  2. PatientDim
  3. PatientDimSourceData
Links from
none
Snapshot on data change
Disabled

    Hcc1DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc1EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 1: HIV/AIDS (98204)

    Data Lineage for Each Package

    HHS-HCC Patients Load
    Hcc18DiagnosisId
    DM_HHS_HCC.HHS_18_PANCREAS_TXP_DX
    Hcc18DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc18EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 18: Pancreas Transplant Status (98215)

    SQL Server data type

    Allows null

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 30: Adrenal, Pituitary, and Other Significant Endocrine Disorders (98224)

    HHS-HCC Patients Load
    Hcc47DiagnosisId
    DM_HHS_HCC.HHS_47_ACU_PANCREA_DX
    Hcc47DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc47EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 47: Acute Pancreatitis (98233)

    DM_HHS_HCC.HHS_67_MYELODYS_SYN_DX
    Hcc67DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc67EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 67: Myelodysplastic Syndromes and Myelofibrosis (98244)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 83: Alcohol Use with Psychotic Complications (98373)

    Hcc106DiagnosisId
    DM_HHS_HCC.HHS_106_TRAUM_COM_LES_C_DX
    Hcc106DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc106EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 106: Traumatic Complete Lesion Cervical Spinal Cord (98263)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 117: Muscular Dystrophy (98273)

    Hcc129DiagnosisId
    DM_HHS_HCC_2.HHS_129_HEART_TXP_DX
    Hcc129DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc129EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 129: Heart Transplant Status/Complications (98283)

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 146: Ischemic or Unspecified Stroke (98293)

    HHS-HCC Patients Load
    Hcc161Diagnosis2Id
    DM_HHS_HCC_2.HHS_161_2_ASTHMA_DX
    Hcc161Diagnosis2IdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc161EpicStatus2

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 161_2: Asthma, Except Severe (98371)

    Allows null

A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 205: Miscarriage with No or Minor Complications (98312)

    HHS-HCC Patients Load
    Hcc226DiagnosisId
    DM_HHS_HCC_2.HHS_226_HIP_FRAC_DX
    Hcc226DiagnosisIdType

    "EpicDiagnosisId"

    Hcc226EpicStatus

    : number

    The status of the HHS-HCC category. The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 226: Hip and Pelvic Fractures (98317)

The status of the category will be calculated as follows: 0 - A diagnosis was found within the search period, but the category should not be included for the patient in the current risk adjustment period. 1 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included, but a higher category already applies to the patient, meaning that this category should not. A category should be included for a patient if: an encounter/invoice was added in the current risk adjustment period, it is an active problem, or the diagnosis date is after any resolved dates for corresponding problems AND it hasn't been marked as Not Applicable (via SDE) since then. 2 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, and a diagnosis has been added to the patient within the current risk adjustment period and therefore does not need to be refreshed. 3 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and it currently applies to the patient, but the diagnosis needs to be refreshed for the current risk adjustment period. 4 - A diagnosis was not found within the search period, but a suspected diagnosis was found. 5 - A diagnosis was found, the category should be included and currently applies to the patient, but the accepted/closed invoice for the encounter did not have a qualifying diagnosis. The category needs to be refreshed for this year. Rule: HHS-HCC 249: Term or Post-Term Singleton Newborn, Normal or High Birthweight (98326)

    Properties

    Data type
    number
    SQL Server data type
    numeric(2,0)
    Allows null
    Yes
